From: Timo Könnecke <mo@mowerk.net>
Date: Thu, 19 Jun 2026 22:15:25 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] nitrous: add bluesleep_hci_event stub

Temporary stopgap to let the nitrous rfkill driver build and load
without a full bluesleep power-management implementation. Bluetooth
low-power sleep is effectively disabled by this stub; proper LPM
support is a follow-up.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [nemo-specific port patch]

diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c b/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c
@@ -569,5 +569,9 @@
 module_init(nitrous_init);
 module_exit(nitrous_exit);
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("Nitrous Oxide Driver for Bluetooth");
 MODULE_AUTHOR("Google");
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
+
+void bluesleep_hci_event(unsigned long event)
+{}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(bluesleep_hci_event);
